<main class="p-8 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
  <div class="mb-6">
    <a href="/" class="btn btn-ghost btn-sm">‚Üê Back to Home</a>
  </div>
  
  <article class="prose lg:prose-xl">
    <h1>Building Static Sites with Phoenix and daisyUI</h1>
    
    <div class="flex gap-2 mb-6">
      <span class="badge badge-primary">Phoenix</span>
      <span class="badge badge-secondary">Elixir</span>
      <span class="badge badge-accent">daisyUI</span>
    </div>
    
    <p class="lead">
      Phoenix Framework combined with daisyUI creates a powerful toolkit for building beautiful static websites with minimal effort.
    </p>
    
    <h2>Why Phoenix for Static Sites?</h2>
    
    <p>
      While Phoenix is known for its real-time capabilities and LiveView, it's also an excellent choice for static site generation. The framework provides:
    </p>
    
    <ul>
      <li>Fast compilation and build times</li>
      <li>Powerful templating with HEEx</li>
      <li>Built-in asset pipeline</li>
      <li>Easy deployment options</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>The Power of daisyUI</h2>
    
    <p>
      daisyUI is a component library built on top of Tailwind CSS. It provides:
    </p>
    
    <div class="alert alert-info my-6">
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" class="stroke-current shrink-0 w-6 h-6"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path></svg>
      <span>daisyUI components are semantic, accessible, and themeable out of the box!</span>
    </div>
    
    <ol>
      <li>Pre-built, beautiful components</li>
      <li>Multiple theme options</li>
      <li>Semantic class names</li>
      <li>Full Tailwind CSS compatibility</li>
    </ol>
    
    <h2>Getting Started</h2>
    
    <p>
      To create your own static Phoenix site with daisyUI, follow these steps:
    </p>
    
    <div class="mockup-code my-6">
      <pre data-prefix="$"><code>mix phx.new my_app --no-ecto --no-live</code></pre>
      <pre data-prefix="$"><code>cd my_app</code></pre>
      <pre data-prefix="$"><code>mix deps.get</code></pre>
      <pre data-prefix="$"><code>mix tailwind.install</code></pre>
    </div>
    
    <h2>Deployment</h2>
    
    <p>
      Once you've built your site, you can deploy it to GitHub Pages, Netlify, Vercel, or any static hosting service. The build process generates a <code>public/</code> directory with all your static assets ready to serve.
    </p>
    
    <div class="card bg-base-200 my-6">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h3 class="card-title">Pro Tip</h3>
        <p>Use GitHub Actions to automate your deployment process. Every push to main can trigger a new build and deployment!</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <h2>Conclusion</h2>
    
    <p>
      Phoenix and daisyUI make a fantastic combination for static site generation. You get the power and flexibility of Phoenix with the beautiful, pre-built components of daisyUI. Happy building!
    </p>
  </article>
</main>
